Pre-Tourney Jank<br />
<br />
For someone that doesn’t write Tournament Reports anymore, I sure am finding myself doing quite a few of these things as of late. I figure it’s a great way to build up some hype of the GPN weekend in Montreal, Quebec planned for the second weekend in January. Foil rings, team cash tournaments (world-cup style) and a PSQ thrown in for a good measure. And if that doesn’t draw you, all of this is being held in a BAR. Should be crazy fun. Recommended hotel: Ruby Foo’s on Decarie (you can get a room for 89 bucks American or so and it’s a 2 minute drive from the event).  Notable names attending the event: The crew from Colorado (McKnight, Hag, Dineagas, etc.), Team Syracuse (Kirk, Steve, etc.), crew from Team USA (Dalton and Tennet), crew from Toronto (Josh, etc.), crew from Ottawa (Jake, Noah, etc.), crew from Quebec City (Brochu, Francis, Hanh, etc.), crew from Montreal (me, Malboeuf(s), Yako, Dominic, etc.) and an honourable mention to (in my view) rookie of the year, Geoff Smith, from Illinois (I think). An event not to be missed. Friday evening is the Foil Ring King Block tourney (this is going to be the biggest showdown between Colorado and Syracuse for dominance in the Block format). Saturday is PSQ, Sunday is World-Cup Team cash tourney. Not to mention that Montreal is THE place to go out for the best pubs and restaurants in Canada (that might not be entirely true, I’m still vetting the statement with Tourism Canada, I’ll get back to you)).<br />
<br />
But anyway now that plug is over with, I thought it would be fun to write up a tournament report for my crazy last-minute planned one-day trip to Syracuse. I can’t believe I’m driving down 4 hours to Syracuse just to play in a Sealed Deck event. I guess it’s because I want to actually give my best shot into winning the Sealed Deck Sprint since I do plan on going to Continentals next year and would like to win that bye. However my Sprint rating is only 1576 and my friend, Fred Côté, is leading with a huge 1619. So with only this last tournament with 5 rounds at 16k, I don’t think I have any shot at winning. But Syracuse is a great place to play cards and I had a blast last year at the TOC so I figure what the hey? Also I haven’t been able to give the sprint my best shot since being banned from my local card shop (once again a big thanks to Dom for that), which has held an unprecedented number of sealed deck events in September and October (when the events were all 32k). So props to Fred for cleaning house and slops to me for not driving 6 hours to make it to more sealed deck events. Maybe next year.<br />
<br />
I used to be a lot better at Sealed Deck play. I’m quite decent at Sealed Deck but have been having more and more trouble with Booster Drafts. I go for combos WAY too often and I should really just sticks to Hobbit Swords and the basics to try and win games. I got really spoiled at my first booster draft when I decided to keep the Pale Blade rare just for fun (cuz I needed one in my collection) and then the next booster I open had a WITCH KING in it. In that same booster draft, I drafted Saruman’s Reach and Return to it’s Master (a nasty combo). It was really fun. So since then, I have been trying for the same moments but instead have been going 0-4 in various booster drafts. Currently my rating is 1715 (not too shabby) which places me second in Quebec and 6th in Canada. Before I actually got any good at this game, I used to take my Sealed Deck rating seriously (hence the King of Sealed label that was slapped on me). But now, I’m much more proud of becoming a decent Constructed Deck player so I’ve let the Sealed Deck play slide a bit. However, I really miss it because I do find that format to be the most fun (with the exception of the ROTK Release Event). And in Syracuse, the players are amazing and fun so I’m really looking forward to this event (and who knows, maybe I’ll end up winning the sprint somehow). <br />
<br />
So the tournament is supposed to start between 2-3 pm in Syracuse. It’s a 4-hour drive and the border has been REALLY bad as of late so I think I’ll just leave to get out there for like noon or 1pm just to be safe. The night before, I’m playtesting at my friend, Steve Judge’s house with Matthew Mitchell and I might as well just take off from there (shaving off half an hour of the trip). I’ve been frantically changing my Standard Format deck over the last 28 days trying to figure out what works best. I’ve built a few decks and then dismantled them after changing my mind without even playing them once. I really need to buckle down and focus on something for the GPN weekend. I’ve got my King Block deck settled but am really at a loss as to what’s best for Standard (although I think it’s Dauntless, I just really don’t want to play that).<br />
<br />
The Longest Day<br />
Saturday, December 13th, 2003<br />
<br />
So after a long evening of playtesting with Steve & Matt, I’m up at 8am and off on my 4-hour drive to Syracuse. The tournament isn’t supposed to start until 3pm but I’m scared of how bad the border crossing can get sometimes so I give myself a wide margin. I swing thru the Tim Horton’s drive-thru, and one large double-double later, I’m fueled and ready to go.<br />
<br />
The drive is uneventful and the U.S. Customs agent waves me thru as soon as I start to say Lord of the Rings. I think it’s easier to get in once they know you don’t have Saddam in the trunk of your car. <br />
<br />
I get to Altered States (card shop) at noon sharp (I made good time!), and it’s this big card shop in an old warehouse. It’s both a gamer’s paradise and girl’s nightmare. After five minutes, I’m already getting uncomfortable by the people there and the owner claiming that there’s no LOTR tournament today. I’m sure he’s wrong and I dial up Kirk England to see if he wants to do lunch. His fiancé, Heather, just put on some cheeseburgers so I jump in the car and make my way over there.<br />
<br />
While killing time before the tournament, I got to play on Kirk’s new x-box. I hadn’t tried Attack of the Clones yet so I gave that a whirl. For some reason I set it to Padawan-difficulty, and even though I was getting shot to pieces, I never died. So it must have been some boring for Kirk to watch. I should have played multi-player. Boo to me.<br />
<br />
So we leave for the tournament around 2 or so, and get there early. I have to time to play a fun casual game of Open with Adam (an ex-rider, I think). Adam moves into Anduin Banks and decides to put the Abracadabra ring on in the maneuver phase even tho Frodo is wound-less. So adding at burden at that particular site 4 is a pretty bad move against Moria and I manage to overwhelm Frodo. Too funny ;)<br />
<br />
So over a little bit of time, familiar faces stroll in. Steve Jones wanders in along with his ‘little’ brother, Dan fresh from his graduation ceremony from college. Seth joins us as well and we’re good to go around 3 p.m. Josh P. doesn’t end up joining us cuz he was in the mood to get a sponge bath from a nurse so he’s throws his blood-sugar out of whack on purpose just to get to the ER. Nice move J<br />
<br />
There are no draft packs finally, so we all get stuck with Aragorn starters from Fellowship of the Ring. There was one Gandalf starter but no one got it (thank goodness). So with everyone having the same starter and 3 boosters, it’s really going to come down to luck with the pulls but, much more important, play skills. Kirk decides as prize support that we’ll snake draft all the rares and foils from everyone’s packs. I end up pulling 5 usable rares (along with Albert Dreary who I can’t use). I pull the rare ring (which I really shouldn’t have played with in the end), STING!, Tale-of-Gil-Galad, CAVE TROLL AND TOLDEA!!! Can you believe those pulls? Luckily I pulled one wallcrawler in my booster pack along with a goblin spear so I am able to play with the troll and set him up for site 5. I also use a host of thousands in case I want to ditch my wallcrawler early. <br />
<br />
I start my first few games with Legolas, Prince and Sam, Son of Hamfast cuz I want to bid 6 and go first. In the end, this is stupid since I have SO many Gondor cards that I should really just start Boromir, SOD and Merry, FOTB since I have 2 Aragorns, KIE, hobbit swords (2) so Merry will be incredible powerful. My first two games, I play with the incorrect starting fellowship and then correct it for the 3 last games. <br />
<br />
Someone pulls a foil servant so that looks to be the best prize for the snake draft.<br />
<br />
Now I can’t seem to remember exactly who I played and in what order so my apologies if the names or rounds are slightly mixed up…<br />
<br />
Round One<br />
Seth<br />
Good: I get out the troll and wallcrawler and site 5. Only wish I could have had the spear.<br />
Bad: Seth had no minions from sites 5-7 allowing me an important double move for free.<br />
Ugly: My Uruk Ragers and Soldiers were only discarding minions on Seth’s side so it was a really easy walk for my fellowship.<br />
Result: FW site 9<br />
<br />
Round Two<br />
Kirk England<br />
Good: This was a great match. My Bred for Battles were coming out at the PERFECT moments. <br />
Bad: I needed one more pool to play with troll at a crucial moment.<br />
Ugly: I didn’t get Gorn or Boromir until site 5 or 6 which really killed my fellowship. This was the catalyst to me changing my starting fellowship.<br />
Result: FL Shadow Kill site 8<br />
<br />
Round 3<br />
College-boy Dan Jones<br />
Good: It was fun playing against the graduate himself. Too much fun.<br />
Bad: Dan had only 2 companions all game, I think.<br />
Ugly: I Stung Dan’s hand and saw that he ALSO pulled a Toldea. My Frodo was at 3 burdens and Sam had died so I couldn’t block with Frodo anymore which really hurt. Dan held onto his Toldea and it was really putting a wrench into my fellowship since I could not allow Frodo to hit 4 burdens. <br />
Result: FW shadow kill site 8<br />
<br />
Round 4<br />
Steve Jones!!!<br />
Good: Steve is the best. This was prolly my most fun match.<br />
Bad: Steve pulls a White Arrows in a booster and proceeds to drive me completely insane with that card. I forgot how annoying that card can be.<br />
Ugly: I have never played with Coat of Mail in my life and played it on Aragorn while he had an Armor on him already. Steve doesn’t notice and then points it out later in the game when I block two uruks on Aragorn and assume I will take one wound only. Steve is like JUDGE! And I’m all worried about making a stupid mistake and getting more stupid warnings but Steve ends up just asking which of the two I want to ditch. I elect the Armor so that Aragorn only takes 3 wounds and is not overwhelmed. I throw the Armor on Boromir for fun but the game is pretty much decided at that point anyway.<br />
Result: FW site 9<br />
<br />
Round 5<br />
Jeff<br />
Good: Jeff was a little sleepy from working the night before so I was happy to take full advantage of the psychological benefit J<br />
Bad: My Uruk Rager discards the top two cards of Jeff’s deck and I make him lose the Witch King! Whew! The rare pulls in this sealed deck tournament are INSANE.<br />
Ugly: Jeff decides to return the favour and defeats one of my companions with his Rager and I flip over my Cave Troll. I was so pissed…<br />
Result: FW shadow kill site 6 due to player error (never start Boromir’s skirmish first when Frodo needs the pump to survive)<br />
<br />
So there is like a 3-way tie for 1st place and the opposition totals are all the same so we end up rolling a d20 to see who wins. I roll a 10, Seth rolls a 6, Kirk rolls a 10. So it’s down to me and Kirk and I really want that foil Servant (Kirk is the guy that offered me a Foil Servant for free in a trade for my Foil Hides but I turned it down so this would be the second time I could have a Foil Servant from kirk). Kirk rolls a 13 and I’m all nervous. I start to roll the die and the adrenaline going thru my veins is wicked awesome. This die roll is easily the most exciting part of the tournament so I think that Wizards of the Coast might have the right idea with their Neopets CCG. I roll the die and it comes up as a six and I scream out loud in anguish. <br />
<br />
Kirk grabs the foil servant and I look at the rest of the rares and foils. There are two common foils and a ton of rares including Goblin Armory, Troll, WitchKing, 2 Toldeas, Tale of Gil-Galad, Underdeeps, Merry FTS. I take a look at everything and take a foil Dwarven Axe just cuz I can’t decide. (also I have 4 of all the other rares). The snake draft comes back to me and there is still a ton of good rares but I take the foil dwarven skirmish common event just for fun. I then give the rest of my draft picks to Dan as a graduation present. The brownie points are well invested here since the next morning, Kirk gives me a Morgul King and new Cantea which I desperate needed. Steve and Dan both give me a Rekindled King which I also need. I hate trading so much since one side always regrets their trade at some point so I usually just give away rares that I don’t intend to play with to my friends. It was great of Kirk to throw me 2 great rares just cuz I really needed them.<br />
<br />
So after this, we all head over to the Spaghetti Warehouse for dinner. I should mention that Heather has been with us the entire time reading a book in the corner waiting for her brother, Ray, to show up (which he finally does just in time for supper). There is like an hour wait for a table so I’m all pissed that no one reserved a table while we were playing cards next door. But they have a bar and I haven’t had Dewar’s scotch in a while so the hour passes quickly. <br />
<br />
We pass a few tables of prom kids on the way to our table and I keep bumping into things while being distracted by all the low-cut dresses and stuff. How embarrassing. Our waitress, Nicole, ends up being crazy hot (and she just keeps getting better and better everytime she comes back to the table), so we have a pretty good time during dinner. I want to order some sort of Italian roast beef sandwich but the guys wave me off it reminding me what happened at Arbys during the TOC last May. Also Nicole tells me the sandwich is ‘OK’ which is the worst adjective food staff is allowed to usually say about one of their own menu items. She then tells me the meatloaf is ‘excellent’ so I opt for that (I’m hoping it’ll wreck me as bad as the last time in Toronto). Ray orders steak and stuffed mushrooms and he definitely made the better picks. <br />
<br />
The bill comes along and Nicole hands it to me but the pen falls out and hits me squarely in the crotch. I react by instinctively shouting out, ‘AH! MY BALLS!’ to the delight of the entire table. Just writing this now is making me laugh out loud remembering the moment. It was pretty priceless. What kind of idiot shouts that out in a restaurant? I’m blaming the Dewar’s.<br />
<br />
So we regroup back at Kirk’s house cuz I really need to take off my Ring-Bound T-shirt which I forgot that I was wearing around the restaurant in front of all the prom chicks. So I throw on Malboeuf’s florescent orange t-shirt which I stole off him sometime last summer. <br />
<br />
The first bar we hit is a cigar bar called Awful Al’s. I haven’t had American cider in a while so that became my beverage of choice for the evening. This place totally reeks of cigar smoke so we end up in the very back playing 6-player darts (Cricket). Dan and I team up and the first game goes very badly for us. My first dart always bounces off the board. It was getting quite predictable. Kirk and Steve take the first game easy. Second game, I can’t seem to not hit the triples and manage to close off half the numbers before the other teams knew what hit them. I’m terrible at the bull’s eye and only manage to hit one. Dan finishes them off and we pull a win. Normally, I’d stay for another one but the cigar smoke is just terrible so we bail and head over to another place called the Bear and Deer Pub or something. <br />
<br />
I should also mention I’m getting I.D.’ed at each location which is wicked cool cuz that never happens to me anymore. This next place is a real dump with some crappy band doing Barenaked Ladies covers (yay Canada). The bartender is like this total jerk cuz when we told him we’d rather get served by the better looking Sarah Michelle Gellar look-alike bus-girl, he got all mad and yelled out, ‘FINE! THEN WAIT!.’As if this doesn’t happen to him all the time. He then gets mad at the bus-girl and sends her off to clean tables. Pretty funny.<br />
<br />
So we leave that place and end up at some really cool irish pub called Kitty Hoynes. The owner is at the door and this guy has like the map of Ireland on his face cuz he looks so gosh darnit Irish. We get to chattin’ and I’m telling him of all the places and pubs in montreal where I’m going to be taking these Syracuse guys (as well as those heavy drinkin’ Colorado bastards) to when they hit up Montreal in 3 weeks. We stay there until pretty much closing (2 am). <br />
<br />
Get back to Kirk’s and Dan is sleeping on the couch so Ray throws this big blanket on his face. I was kinda thinking that waking people up in uncomfortable ways is more of a camp-type thing you do when you’re a teenager. Poor Dan comes to but at least his headache is gone. I tell him to get off the couch cuz that’s where I’m sleeping so he thinks it will be helpful to me if he farts right on my pillow. I switch pillows real fast before the entire couch is compromised. Steve and Ray start up a game but I fall on the couch and am out like a light. <br />
<br />
Everyone crashed at Kirk’s and Heather made us all a killer good breakfast (but no coffee cuz they’re crazy). So as good as the breakfast is, no coffee just won’t do so we head out to Denny’s to catch up with Josh who just got released from the hospital. They ended up giving him meatloaf at the hospital last night so I was mad jealous. I order the Biscuits and Sausage Gravy just for kicks but after one bite, I realize I’ve made a terrible mistake. Josh switches them up for his pancakes and bails me out. <br />
<br />
The worst snow storm has been going on for sometime now so I start my long drive back in terrible weather and get home in time for the Survivor finale. I’m SO happy that Sandra wins the whole thing cuz ‘Lil was just too stupid for words. Sandra has been my first pick ever since Rupert got the boot. Happy ending. Did anybody else catch Rupert’s accidental spoiler for the next All-star Survivor? I can’t believe Jeff didn’t try to cover that up more… anyway…<br />
<br />
Wicked tournament and fun 2-day trip for a local tournament in Syracuse. I even got a Team ‘Cuse t-shirt out of the deal. Can’t wait to see these fellas in Montreal next month.<br />
<br />
Props:<br />
·	Kirk England for putting the tournament together and having me over at his house. Also for doing the driving Saturday night cuz stupid Ray forgot his ID at home.<br />
·	Steve Jones for being the coolest and funniest guy ever. Montreal is so gonna rock.<br />
·	Dan Jones for graduating and teaching me those hilarious handshakes.<br />
·	Seth for getting me to look at his stupid southron deck and giving advice. Don’t play southrons!<br />
·	Heather for letting Kirk have his LOTR-themed living room. And for making second breakfast.<br />
·	Nicole for putting up with our obnoxious table.<br />
·	My winter tires for keeping me alive<br />
·	Jeff for playing in the tournament and coming out with us even tho he was exhausted<br />
·	John Irving for being a great player and a fantastic guy. See you on the other side, buddy.<br />
<br />
Slops:<br />
·	Josh for being at a hospital instead of the tournament. Stop getting sick! You better not miss Montreal cuz we’re so hitting up the Bar-B Barn for the best ribs in the city.<br />
·	The bartender at the Bear & Deer pub<br />
·	The weather<br />
·	Altered States for not having draft packs<br />
